    Package Description
    hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.impl.commands  

    • Uses of Command in hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.impl.commands

      Classes in hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.impl.commands that implement Command 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  ColorCommand
      The command is used to set the color of the current TurtleState of the Context.
      class  DrawCommand
      The command is used to draw the next line - length of step in the current direction of the turtle.
      class  PopCommand
      The command is used to remove the current TurtleState from the Context.
      class  PushCommand
      The command is used to add a new TurtleState to the Context.
      class  RotateCommand
      Command used for changing the direction of the current TurtleState.
      class  ScaleCommand
      Updates the effective step size by multiplying by factor scale.
      class  SkipCommand
      Skip command - moves the turtle in the current direction of the turtle and updates the positon of the turtle but doesn't draw a line.
